    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>EXXON TO GET $300 MILLION IN A PARTIAL SETTLEMENT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">AP</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Exxon Corporation said yesterday that it would receive $300 million from  Lloyd's of London and about 250 other underwriters in a partial settlement of a  lawsuit to recover expenses from the 1989 Exxon Valdez oil spill in Alaska. Exxon had sought more than $1 billion from its insurance companies and underwriting syndicates for the tanker accident and oil spill. The insurers refused to pay, saying the accident was caused by the company's negligence. The company, based in Irving, Tex., still has $250 million in unresolved claims  pending with Lloyd's and other underwriters. Exxon spent $3 billion to clean up  the spill and to settle lawsuits.</p>
      </block>
